The president does not want to avoid this topic because he is aware that he receives this award by being a president who is waging a war in two countries at the moment.
He stepped up the war effort a few days ago by sending additional units to Afghanistan, which none of his critics will forget to point out.
During the ceremony, Obama will also receive a gold medal, a diploma and a cheque of ten million Swedish kronor (about 1.1 million Euros).
He intends to donate it to charities, but has not yet decided which ones.
His program will then take him and his wife to a banquet including, in addition to the King and Queen of Norway, the head of government and 250 other guests.
Obama was rather reluctant at that price at first.
For example, he mentioned having the feeling that he did not fully deserve it.
