The first dose of vaccine should be administered between the 3rd and 5th month of the child.
Last year, a quarter of families voluntarily vaccinated their children against pneumococcal disease.
Yet the parents paid 1,600 crowns or more for a dose.
Vaccination of the youngest requires four doses.
Experts estimate that every year health insurance costs 300 to 450,000 crowns in vaccine doses.
However, they save on the medical care that unvaccinated children would require.
So far, the state has spent about 500,000 crowns a year on all child vaccination.
The reimbursed vaccination was introduced with the "Janota package".
Pneumococci are the cause of inflammation of the middle ear but also of serious infections including meningitis and blood poisoning.
