The UN-sponsored climate conference -- characterized so far by disorganized allocations and mutual recriminations -- returned to the limelight on Friday, due to the publication of a document highlighting the ambitious reductions in greenhouse gases over the next 40 years, with industrialized nations shouldering most of the burden.
